 ('50', '56', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<h3>Initial brief:</h3>\r\n<p><small>A worldwide directory of user rated yoga classes.</small></p>\r\n<h3>What it morphed into:</h3>\r\n<p><small>A user rated yoga directory of classes, teachers and events with a strong emphasis on community involvement. <em>Plus a killer feature:</em> &nbsp;let teachers run their practice without being beholden to yoga studios (major hints from Uber/Airbnb).</small></p>', NULL, '0', '0', '', '0', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', '0', '2017-10-25 03:21:39', '2017-11-08 01:37:06', '1141a9df-78b6-4d10-b14b-9125ad6a6eed'),
 ('52', '58', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '0', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', '0', '2017-10-25 09:39:51', '2017-11-08 01:37:06', 'dce6775c-5c91-4522-b6b4-baeb4465629e'),
 ('53', '59', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Finding a good yoga class is harder than it needs to be.</strong> Where do you start? Probably Google. You filter down to the best rated yoga studios that are close by. Read a few of the reviews. Looks good! &nbsp;Then you jump onto their website only to realise their classes aren\'t a good fit and they\'re all at the wrong times. ⬅️&nbsp; Back, repeat... ⬅️&nbsp; Back, repeat... &#x1f616;</p>\r\n<p><strong>My Role:</strong>&nbsp;Product Designer</p>\r\n<ul><li>Requirements capture via stakeholder interviews (business goals & job stories)</li><li>Competitor Research</li><li>Project scope and delivery schedule</li><li>Value proposition improvements</li><li>Job Stories and User Flows</li><li>Wireframes</li><li>Branding</li><li>High fidelity desktop & mobile designs</li><li>Prototyping</li><li>Styleguide for dev handover</li><li>Overseeing dev implementation and tech stack decisions</li></ul>', NULL, '0', '0', 'intro', '0', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', '0', '2017-10-25 09:39:51', '2017-11-08 01:37:06', '5bfdf853-468d-492b-be43-181792ad5d8f'),
 ('54', '60', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', NULL, '0', '0', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', '0', '2017-10-25 10:00:33', '2017-11-08 01:37:06', '5bd00ca6-a530-49f5-a4da-e61fedc2523e'),
 ('55', '62', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<h2>Research</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Initial brief:&nbsp;</strong>A worldwide desktop website directory of user rated yoga classes.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Competitor analysis:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul><li><strong>Google / Yelp Searches:</strong> no option to see class times. Reviews of the yoga studio only. What happens if a teacher moves?</li><li><strong>Mindbody:</strong> Nicely designed app, but no option to filter apart from distance which makes searches hit or miss. Not specific to yoga, which isn\'t a a bad thing. Great market penetration both here and abroad. Offers package deals & specials (something to think about). Focus is on studios rather than individual teachers so the reviews become less relevant.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Friend recommendations:</strong> in person or on social media. Hit or miss.</li><li><strong>Yoga studio websites:&nbsp;</strong>Only offers their classes and teachers (obvious).&nbsp;No reviews unless you google them first. Some allow you to book online, others do not.</li><li><strong>Other misc directory websites:&nbsp;</strong>there are a bunch of them, but most are poorly designed (good luck on mobile). Offer limited filtering and usually no reviews. Cannot book directly through site.</li></ul>', NULL, '0', '0', '', '0', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', '0', '2017-10-25 12:05:20', '2017-11-08 01:37:06', '29269b83-a06c-4aa8-a225-dcba9642e377'),
 ('56', '63', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Teacher insights:</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<ul><li>It\'s expensive and hard to attract clientele as a solo operator so being employed by one or many yoga studios is the most realistic option.</li><li>Generally teach at 3 or more locations, making scheduling a challenge.</li><li>Median teacher salary in Australia $30.84 per hour.</li></ul>\r\n<p><strong>Student insights:</strong></p>\r\n<ul><li>\"I find most studios and classes extremely intimidating.\"&nbsp;<br><em>Teachers should be notified of new students so special attention can be paid.</em></li><li>\"I\'ve been to a few classes here and then, but it\'s been a bit meh\".&nbsp;<br><em>Bad teacher or wrong type of class: fixed with reviews and better filtering?</em></li><li>\"That\'s something girls do. Not for me.\"&nbsp;<br><em>Maybe we should encourage teachers to tailor specific classes to be more inclusive or appealing to certain groups. What role does marketing play?</em></li><li>\"Yoga class can feel like a lonely place - you go, sweat for a bit and then that\'s it. I\'m too nervous to ask questions\".&nbsp;<br><em>How do we create a sense of community inside and outside of the classroom?&nbsp;</em></li><li>\"I always forget to bring cash with me so I have to rush to the ATM before a class\". <br><em>Add online bookings. Simple.</em></li></ul>\r\n<p>Armed with plenty of insights, we now had our project scope. To further refine, <a href=\"https://blog.intercom.com/using-job-stories-design-features-ui-ux/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Job Stories</a> were created for a single source of truth and to reveal anything missed. This brings us to a (long) elevator pitch:<br></p>\r\n<ul><li>At the core, Flow should be a mobile & desktop app bringing together yoga teachers and students, with a strong emphasis on becoming THE destination for yoga classes and teacher reviews. Reviews are everything.</li><li>Give users the option to filter by multiple fields so they can really narrow down their search to find the perfect match.&nbsp;</li><li>Let\'s add the ability to book a class - it\'s the perfect revenue stream and easy to implement with a service like <a href=\"http://stripe.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Stripe</a>. It\'s an easy revenue win for both teachers and Flow, and makes student\'s lives easier - who carries around cash these days?</li><li>Make it a mobile app: teachers can keep track of class numbers and revenue. Students can be notified when a class is about to start, or to re-engage those that have lost interest. Aim should be a hybrid approach: responsive website for desktop and mobile (good for SEO), direct users to&nbsp;native apps&nbsp;on android + iOS (react/angular)&nbsp;for a better experience.</li><li>Provide a direct line of communication from student to teacher outside of the classroom. Encourage teachers to share insights and resources to further student engagement.</li></ul>\r\n<p>There are other factors to consider as well:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul><li>Beyond making it super simple & fast, how do we get yoga teachers to join and list their classes.</li><li>What about yoga studios? How do we include them into the picture.</li><li>How does roll out happen - per city, per country... another metric?</li><li>How is success measured and what are attainable targets to attract future investment?</li></ul>', NULL, '0', '0', '', '0', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', '0', '2017-10-25 12:05:20', '2017-11-08 01:37:06', '89eaebad-b78f-4edb-80fc-0f46132a9343'),
