otypes, including validation & refinement<\\/li><li>Styleguide for dev handover<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"56\":{\"modified\":\"1\",\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"0\",\"collapsed\":\"1\",\"level\":\"0\",\"fields\":{\"highlight\":\"\",\"cssClasses\":\"\",\"paragraph\":\"<h3>Initial brief:<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p><small>A worldwide directory of user rated yoga classes.<\\/small><\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>What it morphed into:<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p><small>A user rated yoga directory of classes, teachers and events with a strong emphasis on community involvement. <em>Plus a killer feature:<\\/em> &nbsp;let teachers run their practice without being beholden to yoga studios (major hints from Uber\\/Airbnb).<\\/small><\\/p>\"}},\"62\":{\"modified\":\"1\",\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"collapsed\":\"0\",\"level\":\"0\",\"fields\":{\"highlight\":\"\",\"cssClasses\":\"\",\"paragraph\":\"<h2>Research<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><strong>Initial brief:&nbsp;<\\/strong>A worldwide desktop website directory of user rated yoga classes.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Competitor analysis:&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li><strong>Google \\/ Yelp Searches:<\\/strong> no option to see class times. Reviews of the yoga studio only (what if a teacher moves).<\\/li><li><strong>Mindbody:<\\/strong> Overall a fairly good user experience, but no option to filter apart from distance. Not specific to yoga, which isn\'t a a bad thing. Great market penetration both here and abroad. Offers deals. Focus is on studios rather than individual teachers.<\\/li><li><strong>Friend recommendations:<\\/strong> in person or on social media. Hit or miss.<\\/li><li><strong>Yoga studio websites:&nbsp;<\\/strong>Only offers their classes and teachers (duh!).&nbsp;No reviews. Some allow you to book online, others do not.<\\/li><li><strong>Other misc directory websites:&nbsp;<\\/strong>there are a bunch of them, but most are poorly designed (good luck on mobile). Offer limited filtering and usually no reviews. Cannot book directly through site.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"96\":{\"modified\":\"1\",\"type\":\"gallery\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"collapsed\":\"0\",\"level\":\"0\",\"fields\":{\"images\":{\"0\":\"97\",\"focus-attr\":[{\"data-focus-x\":\"0.00\",\"data-focus-y\":\"0.00\"}]}}},\"63\":{\"modified\":\"1\",\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"collapsed\":\"0\",\"level\":\"0\",\"fields\":{\"highlight\":\"\",\"cssClasses\":\"\",\"paragraph\":\"<p><strong>Teacher insights:<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>It\'s expensive and hard to attract clientele as a solo operator so being employed by one or many yoga studios is the realistic option for most.<\\/li><li>Generally teach at 3 or more locations, making scheduling a challenge.<\\/li><li>Median teacher salary in Australia $30.84 per hour.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<p><strong>Student insights:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>\\\"I find most studios and classes extremely intimidating.\\\"&nbsp;<em>Teachers should be notified of new students so special attention can be paid.<\\/em><\\/li><li>\\\"I\'ve been to a few classes here and then, but it\'s been a bit meh\\\".&nbsp;<em>Bad teacher or wrong type of class: fixed with reviews and better filtering?<\\/em><\\/li><li>\\\"That\'s something girls do. Not for me.\\\"&nbsp;<em>Maybe we should encourage teachers to tailor specific classes to be more inclusive or appealing to certain groups. Can marketing help?<\\/em><\\/li><li>\\\"Yoga class can feel like a lonely place - you go, sweat for a bit and then that\'s it. I\'m too nervous to ask questions\\\".&nbsp;<em>How do we create a sense of community inside and outside of the classroom?&nbsp;<\\/em><\\/li><li>\\\"I always forget to bring cash with me so I have to rush to the ATM before a class\\\". <em>Add online bookings.<\\/em><\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Armed with plenty of insights, we now had our project scope. To further refine, <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/blog.intercom.com\\/using-job-stories-design-features-ui-ux\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noreferrer noopener\\\">Job Stories<\\/a> were created for a single source of truth and to reveal anything missed. This brings us to our (slight long) elevator pitch:<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>At the core, Flow should be a mobile & desktop app bringing together yoga teachers and students, with a strong emphasis on becoming the destination for yoga classes and teacher reviews. Reviews are everything.<\\/li><li>Give users the option to filter by multiple fields so they can really narrow down their search to find the perfect match.&nbsp;<\\/li><li>Let\'s add the ability to book a class - it\'s the perfect revenue stream and easy to implement with a service like <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/stripe.com\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noreferrer noopener\\\">Stripe<\\/a>. Who carries around cash these days?&nbsp;<\\/li><li>A mobile app for a service like Flow is a clear winner: teachers can keep track of class numbers and revenue. Students can be notified when a class is about to start, or to re-engage those that have lost interest.<\\/li><li>Provide a direct line of communication from student to teacher outside of the classroom. Encourage teachers to share insights and resources to further student engagement.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\"}},\"99\":{\"modified\":\"1\",\"type\":\"gallery\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"collapsed\":\"0\",\"level\":\"0\",\"fields\":{\"images\":{\"0\":\"98\",\"focus-attr\":[{\"data-focus-x\":\"0.00\",\"data-focus-y\":\"0.00\"}]}}},\"64\":{\"modified\":\"1\",\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"collapsed\":\"0\",\"level\":\"0\",\"fields\":{\"highlight\":\"\",\"cssClasses\":\"\",\"paragraph\":\"<h2>Mockups<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>High fidelity mockups.<br>Prototypes<\\/p>\"}},\"65\":{\"modified\":\"1\",\"type\":\"gallery\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"collapsed\":\"0\",\"level\":\"0\",\"fields\":{\"images\":{\"0\":\"92\",\"1\":\"91\",\"2\":\"93\",\"3\":\"90\",\"4\":\"89\",\"focus-attr\":[{\"data-focus-x\":\"0.00\",\"data-focus-y\":\"0.00\"},{\"data-focus-x\":\"0.00\",\"data-focus-y\":\"0.00\"},{\"d